<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,417,840]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,384,417,443]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Material examined.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation box="[390,1102,418,444]" country="Japan" location="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" specimenCount="1">
About 1610 specimens, including the 
<typeStatus box="[809,857,418,444]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">type</typeStatus>
series, all from 
<collectingCountry box="[1035,1102,418,444]" name="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Japan</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
. No specimens were available from the Russian Far East and 
<collectingCountry box="[496,568,454,480]" name="South Korea" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1318,489,516]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,417,840]" box="[199,1318,489,516]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,489,515]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,434,490,516]" name="Russia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[448,630,490,516]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[649,713,490,516]" name="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[727,842,490,516]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, Kunashiri Is., Honshu) (Sundukov 2009).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,417,840]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,526,552]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Host plant</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1822" box="[340,467,526,552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Spach) Turcz. ex Rupr." authorityName="Rupr." baseAuthorityName="Spach" box="[478,910,526,552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis box="[478,629,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Alnus hirsuta</emphasis>
(Spach) Turcz. ex Rupr.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thunb.) Steud." authorityName="Steud." baseAuthorityName="Thunb." box="[921,1276,526,552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis box="[921,1091,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Alnus japonica</emphasis>
(Thunb.) Steud.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="572" refId="ref77555" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (1995) A new host record for Pamphilius itoi (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Japanese Journal of Entomology, Tokyo, 63, 572." type="journal article" year="1995">Shinohara &amp; Hara 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 2005).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,417,840]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,598,624]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is often commonly found in 
<collectingRegion box="[796,909,598,624]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[922,986,598,624]" name="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Japan</collectingCountry>
(1436 Japanese specimens recorded by National Museum of Nature and Science 2021), but only 
<specimenCount box="[799,935,634,660]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
have been recorded from the continent (
<collectingRegion country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[308,386,670,696]" name="Russia" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Russia</collectingCountry>
, by Sundukov 2009). We have seen no specimens of this species from outside 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1331,670,696]" name="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,417,840]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
In the molecular analysis using COI and NaK (
<figureCitation box="[736,838,706,732]" captionStart="FIGURE 149" captionStartId="236.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,198,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@236.[163,1425,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="236" captionText="FIGURE 149. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876861/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Figs 149</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[851,896,706,732]" captionStart="FIGURE 160" captionStartId="245.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1406,188,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-19@245.[171,1416,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="245" captionText="FIGURE 160. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876884/files/figure.png" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">160</figureCitation>
), the specimens of this species (all from 
<collectingCountry box="[1363,1429,706,732]" name="Japan" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Japan</collectingCountry>
) were retrieved as a clade belonging to a complex of rather poorly resolved 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Hara" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[985,1049,742,768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[985,1049,742,768]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Alnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- and 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1185,742,768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1185,742,768]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Betula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-feeding species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,236,778,804]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[151,236,778,804]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[406,539,778,804]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnivorus">
<emphasis box="[406,539,778,804]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">P. alnivorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
